Description: As the name suggest water-war is a game in which player are fighting using water. They will be given water balloons to attack the opponent. IF THE PAPER DISK BREAKS THEN THAT PLAYER WILL OUT. At last the team having maximum number of players that team will be declared as winner.

• Physical touch will not be allowed to opposite team members.
• The player with water balloons will be given LIMITED SPACE and other players will be given whole space.
• 4 players with water balloons have to attack the opponent team below his head. And if they attack with high speed they will be out.

Description:
The basic idea of the event is questionnaire. The questionnaire would be carried by simultaneously distracting the participants. The level of distraction would vary from round to round. The questions asked in first two rounds will be multiple choice type questions. The last round will be a rapid fire round. The distractions in the rounds may vary depending on the innovative ideas regarding distraction.

Round 1:-
The participants will be expected to answer few questions depending on the 
Topic they choose simultaneously facing the distraction. The distraction involved in this round is being able to eat bun without having water with it. The least scorer will be eliminated. At the end of this round 3 out of 4 participants will move to next round

Round 2:-
In round 2, participants will be again asked few questions or solve puzzles facing distractions of increased level from round 1. Distraction in this round involves wrapping the cloth on their mouth tightly and allowing them to turn around themselves simultaneously while answering question or solving puzzle. At the end one who scores least will be eliminated. The remaining 2 participants will be considered as two finalists.

Round 3:-
In round 3, level of questions would be raised which would itself be a type of distraction. It will be like a rapid fire round. Common questions will be asked to both participants. The one who will answer true most of the questions at the end will be considered as winner of the event "Distraction".
Title: Distraction

Description:
Offense:  Terrorist Side

Defense Counter-Terrorist Side

Round: One 1 minute 45 second cycle on a map

Half time: The period between halves in which teams swap sides

Match: First team to win 16 total rounds, or the single overtime round

de_dust2

Description:
Dota 2 (Defense of the Ancients) is played in matches between two five-player teams, each of which occupies a stronghold in a corner of the playing field. A team wins by destroying the other side's "Ancient" building, located within the opposing stronghold. Each player controls one of 111 playable "Hero" characters that feature unique powers and styles of play. Each Hero's method of combat is influenced by its primary "attribute": Strength, Agility or Intelligence. During a match, the player collects gold, items, and experience points for their Hero, while combating Heroes of the opposite team. Items are objects sold by shops that provide an ability, bonus, or other function not tied to a particular Hero. They come in a multitude of forms and types, and as such can be very different from one item to the next. Items take up space in a Hero's Inventory, meaning only six can be carried at one time.
The Dire and Radiant occupy strongholds in opposite corners of the playing field, divided by a river. Within each base is a critical structure called the "Ancient", along with a fountain that regenerates Heroes' health and magic points. A match ends when one side breaches the other's stronghold and destroys the Ancient therein. The two strongholds are connected by three paths, referred to as "lanes", which are guarded by defensive towers and artificially intelligent creatures called "creeps". These creatures periodically spawn in groups and travel along the lanes to attack enemy Heroes, creeps and buildings. Also present are "neutral creeps" hostile to both Radiant and Dire, the most powerful of which is "Roshan", a boss that may be killed by either side to obtain a powerful reward.
All Games
Team Size: 5
Mode: Captain's Mode
Map: Tournament Version
Spectating: Disabled
Single Elimination Bracket
Participants & Teams

Every real person - unless officially banned - with a valid steam account is allowed to participate in the competition and will be called "participant" in the following. Five participants will form together a team and enter the competition.
Title: Dota 2

Description:
This event will be organized into five different phases and each phase contains different tasks and challenges.

Phase1: Find The Way.(Testing Your Quick Wits)
In this phase a person is given a maze pattern in which he/she has to solve and find out the way from source to destination. Only pen is allowed to draw the path and no one can undo if it had dawn the wrong path. It is just like the game we were used to play in our childhood.

Phase 2: Riddles. (Testing Your Common Sense & IQ).
In this phase a person is given some riddles to test their common sense and IQ.

Phase 3: Rebus Puzzles (Testing Your Imagination).
In this phase a person is given some pictorial words indicating the meaning of some useful word. The person has to find out that word.

Phase 4: Logical Approach (Testing Your Problem Solving)
In this phase you are given some of the problem solving questions and you have to solve them.

Phase 5: Solving One Face of Rubik’s Cube. (Testing Your Mind Fatigue) 
In this Phase you have to solve any one color of your choice on the Rubik’s Cube.
Rule:
• There are total five phase in each round with the different credit numbers.
• Each round will have maximum 10 participants. 
• There will be total fixed time for first 4 phases. No time limit for individual phases.
• Separate time limit will be for fifth phase.
• In total all phases must be completed as quickly as possible in least time. 
• Each and every phase have different credits as per its difficulty level.
